name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI Thin'.

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansGujaratiUI-Light', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Gujarati UI Medium Regular (NotoSansGujaratiUI-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI Medium'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI SemiBold'.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansGujaratiUI-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Gujarati UI ExtraBold Regular (NotoSansGujaratiUI-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI ExtraBold'.

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Gujarati UI Black'.
